{ [Welcome to the Grünfeld Supercharged!]This course presents a complete  GM-level repertoire  against  1.d4, 1.c4 and 1.Nf3  based on the Grünfeld. This is one of the most reliable and ambitious defenses at Black's disposal.     This repertoire is:    🔵  Ambitious . The lines I propose not only equalize, but the resulting positions also allow Black to  fight for the full point . Wherever possible, I've avoided forced repetitions or drawish positions }{ (you're welcome!) }{ .    🔵  Practical . With about  300 trainable variations , you can quickly master }{ (and remember!) }{ this repertoire. There's absolutely no need to learn 1000s of variations to play the Grünfeld at the GM-level, let alone at club-level!    🔵  Innovative . All the analysis presented is  cutting-edge  and was powered by the latest versions of the best neural network engines Stockfish and Leela running on superfast cloud servers. Inside the course, you'll find a whole array of novelties that'll take your opponent out of his preparation and give you the upper hand.    🔵  Comprehensive . This is much more than an opening course. Apart from opening theory, you get standalone chapters on key middlegame and endgame themes  as well as typical tactical puzzles  jampacked with instructive value. Carefully studying these chapters is sure to take your Grünfeld game to the next level!    
Finally, I’ve completely  neutralized  anti-Grünfeld recommendations from various top GMs, including suggestions in Lifetime Repertoires here on Chessable. Be sure to check out the repertoire clashes  files for more details.    As in all of my courses, you can count on a  high support level . I will promptly answer any questions you have and regularly update the course with new theoretical developments.     That's all for the intro, I hope you enjoy the course and have great success with this repertoire!     Alex 'Chessforlife' Belsley  }1. --
