{ [How to study this course?]I’ve structured this course so it can be useful to players from a large variety of over the board }{ (OTB) }{ rating ranges while making best use of Chessable’s MoveTrainer® technology:    🟡 Intermediate players with  OTB rating      I recommend you first focus on the Quickstarter and Key middlegame & endgame chapters. In terms of theory, the priority lines marked with the blue priority tag should be more than sufficient. Please check out this  informational line for how to best use the priority line feature.    🟠 Advanced players with  1800 - 2200 OTB rating      I recommend you start with the Key middlegame & endgame themes chapter and Quickstarter guides, followed by learning the priority lines and only then tackle the full set of trainable lines.    ⚫ Ambitious or master-level players with  rating > 2100     I recommend that you learn all the trainable and alternative trainable lines, which are shaded in red. The latter lines aren’t actually alternatives, but lines you can  opt to train  that go deeper or that cover less popular moves. I’ve titled them according to the following nomenclature:    •  &#91 extra XX &#93  - This alternative trainable line on the move XX is designed to cover an  extra, less popular move  than the regular trainable line directly preceding it. The content here is typically given as a  blue clickable  in the regular trainable line above it.    •  &#91 details XX &#93  - This alternative trainable line on the move XX is designed to cover the position in  more detail  than the preceding trainable line.    
If anything is unclear, don’t hesitate in dropping me a line. I’d love to hear how you find this course structure in the Comments & Notes box below! }1. --
