{ [Priority lines feature]This course contains the Priority lines feature. About a  third  of the total number of lines were marked as  priority  based on their popularity (according to both the Mega and Lichess databases) and instructive value.     Must-do:  change the  Priority type  option from Algorithm selection to  Author selection  in the course menu on the right-hand side of the chapter view.    There are then two ways to make use of this feature:     Option }{ (1) }{ :     You can activate the  Priority Only  feature under the  Learn  tab on the Course Settings menu. To make sure all the key moves work, you should then select the option  All moves  instead of  Key moves  undert the  Study  tab.    More details can be found in the following Chessable blog post:  https://www.chessable.com/blog/priority-lines/      Option }{ (2) }{ - my recommendation!     I recommend  not  activating the aforementioned options and, instead, going through all the variations first and then using the  blue Priority tag  as a reference throughout the study of this course. You can  pause  all the non-priority lines plus anything else you don't find relevant. This allows you to tailor the course to your preferences/level and maximize the efficiency in reviewing the lines you deem most useful. }1. --
