{ The vast majority of the lines in the course are the result of original analysis with the latest versions of Stockfish and Leela running on fast cloud servers.    I made extensive use of correspondence and high-level OTB games. I also paid close attention to the most popular replies at the club level by checking the Lichess online database.     Engines:  latest versions of Stockfish and Leela Chess     Databases:  MegaDatabase, CorrBase, Lichess database     Books/DVDs/Courses:     • 1.d4 for Ambitious Chess Improvers - Angelika Valkova and Gyula Pap    • 1.Nf3: The Reversed Queen's Indian - Yuriy Krykun    • A Killer Chess Opening Repertoire - Aaron Summerscale and Sverre Johnsen    • A Practical Repertoire for White with 1.d4 and 2.c4 - Alexei Kornev    • Alex Banzea's London System - Alex Banzea    • An Attacking Repertoire for White with 1.d4 - Viktor Moskalenko    • Break the Rules: Play the Trompowsky! - Kamil Plitcha    • Calm and collected: 1.d4 - Marko Makaj    • Cheparinov's 1.d4! - Vol.1 King's Indian & Grünfeld - Ivan Cheparinov    • Fighting the Grünfeld with Harry - InfiniteFlash    • Grandmaster Repertoire 11: Beating 1.d4 sidelines - Boris Avrukh    • Grandmaster Repertoire 2A: 1.d4 King's Indian & Grünfeld - Boris Avrukh    • Grandmaster Repertoire 8: The Grünfeld Defence Vol. I - Boris Avrukh    • Grandmaster Repertoire 9: The Grünfeld Defence Vol. II - Boris Avrukh    • Kaufman's New Repertoire for Black and White - Larry Kaufman    • Keep it Simple: 1.d4 - Christof Sielecki    • Lifetime Repertoires: 1.c4/1.Nf3 Part 1 - Carsten Hansen and Christof Sielecki    • Lifetime Repertoires: Alonso's Catalan - Àlvar Alonso Rosell    • Lifetime Repertoires: Jobava London - Hans Niemann    • Lifetime Repertoires: King's Indian Attack - Kamil Plichta    • Lifetime Repertoires: London System - Le Quang Liem    • Lifetime Repertoires: Neo-Catalan Part 2 - Sam Shankland    • Lifetime Repertoires: Peter Svidler's Grünfeld    • Lifetime Repertoires: Plichta's Trompowsky    • Lifetime Repertoires: Sam Shankland's 1.d4 - Part 2    • Lifetime Repertoires: Sahaj & Srinath's London    • Lifetime Repertoires: Swiercz's 1.d4 Part 1     • Lifetime Repertoires: The Catalan - Srinath Narayanan    • Play 4.Bg5 against the Grünfeld - Kiril Georgiev    • Playing the Grünfeld - Alexey Kovalchuk    • Repertorios de por vida: 1.d4 Parte 1 - David Martinez    • The Agile London System - Alfonso Holmes and Oscar Rodriguez    • The Beginner's 1.d4 Repertoire - Andras Toth    • The Harry Attack: Fighting Kingside Fianchettos after 1.d4 - Simon Williams and Richard Palliser    • The Iron English: Botvinnik Variation - Simon Williams and Richard Palliser    • The Jobava London system - Simon Williams    • The London Attack: an ambitious repertoire - IndrekR    • The London System: Essential theory - John Bartholomew and Daniel Barrish    • The London System with 2.Bf4 - Simon Williams     • The Modernized Grünfeld Defense - Yaroslav Zherebukh    • The Principled Queen's Gambit - Part 2 - Daniel Barrish    • The Reti: Nimzo-Larsen Attack - Dalton Perrine and Yaroslav Zherebukh    • The Safest Grünfeld Reloaded - Alexander Delchev    • The Solid 1.d4 - Part 2 - Adrien Demuth    • Understanding the Grünfeld - Jonathan Rowson }1. --
