{ Byrne thought White was in great shape in this position. After all, Black's queen on  b6  and the knight on  c3  are hanging.     What brilliant move did Fischer, playing Black, have in store? }17. Be6{ An astonishing retreating move that Byrne missed. Such is the beauty of this move that it was labelled  the counter of the century . }( { Byrne mentioned he was expecting }17...Nb5? { which he planned to meet with the tactical shot }18.Bxf7+! { when }( {  (a)    }18...Kxf7 19.Qb3+ Be6 20.Ng5++- { wins. } )( {  (b)    }18...Kh8 19.Bxb6 Nxa3 20.Bxe8 axb6 21.Bf7± { leaves White up an exchange. } ) )
18. Bxe6{ This allows Black to deliver a glorious smothered mate. }
18. Qb5+
19. Kg1( 19.Ke1 Qe2 { is checkmate. } )
19. Ne2+
20. Kf1
20. Ng3+
21. Kg1
21. Qf1+
22. Rxf1
22. Ne2{ Now that the king is entombed by the rooks, the knight delivers the coup de grâce. }( { That would have been quite an ending. Byrne of course saw all this and instead played   }18.Bxb6 { Head onto the next puzzle to see how the game turned out. } )
