4. Bf4{ is one of the most solid variations in the Grünfeld. White develops the bishop outside the pawn chain before bolstering the  d4  pawn with  e2 - e3 . The bishop is also well placed on  f4 , fighting for the critical  e5  square and keeping tabs on the  c7  pawn. }
