13. f5{ A well-known reaction. Here's another  rule of thumb  when countering the Botvinnik setup: whenever White goes  f2 - f4 , Black should be ready to meet it with ... f5 . This puts a stop to any ideas White had of gaining space on the kingside with  g4  and  f5 .     Black is very comfortable and will likely follow-up with ... Nec6  and ... Rae8 . In the long run, we can look to engineer the ... e5  break. }
