17. Ba6{ An over the board novelty, so far only played in the correspondence game ½-½ }{ (31) }{ Tomilin,A }{ (2300) }{ -Palladino,M }{ (2304) }{ ICCF email 2021. It's also a very logical move, Black seeks to exchange the bishops to weaken the light-squares. In particular, Black would love to drop the  a5  knight into  c4 .     Another benefit of ... Ba6  is vacating the  b7  square such that  Rc1  can now simply be met with ... Qb7 .    17... Ba6  was  not  considered in the Chessable course  Lifetime Repertoires: Swiercz's 1.  d4  - Part 1 . }
