12. f5{ Black expands on the kingside in true King's Indian spirit. The immediate threat is ... f5 - f4 , which White must address. }
13. Qc2( 13.exf5 { is a pawn White quickly regretted taking in the game 0-1 (32) Thorfinnsson,B (2387)-Gretarsson, H (2579) Gardabaer 2020, which continued }13...gxf5 14.Bh6 { and here }14...e4! { is a small improvement over the game's 14... Qd8 .      Note:  you can opt to train this clickable line in the upcoming  alternative trainable line. } )
13. f4{ In contrast to the  13.Qe2  variation, this move works really well here as White does not have enough control over the  b5  square. }
