7. Qa4+{ which has been picking up in popularity. It's a serious move that featured in well over 1600 OTB games. }( 7.Bb5+ { is another check aimed at disrupting Black's typical development. It has been seen in 1700+ OTB games. } )( { We'll also examine the rarer dark-squared bishop sorties }7.Bg5 { and }7.Ba3 { , which have been essayed in hundreds of games. } )( 7.Be3 { is likely to transpose to the  7.Nf3  c5  8.Be3  variation covered in the previous chapter . }7...c5 8.Qd2 Qa5 { As usual, Black brings out the queen to  a5  before castling in the  Be3  systems! }9.Rc1 O-O 10.Nf3 Nd7 { transposes to the 7.Nf3 8.Be3  chapter. } )( {   }9.Rb1 { is the only independent option addressed in this chapter. } )
