10. Bb5+{ is by far the most popular move. White throws in a check on  b5  to provoke ... Bd7  and thus rule out ... Bb7/a6 , the latter being more active squares for the bishop. }( {  (a)  }10.Rc1 { White has merely wasted a tempo with  Rb1  followed by  Rc1 . }10...O-O 11.Nf3 Bb7 12.d5 Nd7 { with ideas of ... Nf6  and ... f5  gives Black fantastic play. } )( {  (b)  }10.Rb5 { is simply bypassed with }10...Qa4 { when }11.Rb1 { with the obvious threat of  Bb5 + is neutralized by }11...Ba6 { . } )
