11. O-O{ Black will likely play ... Nc6  next with standard play against White's center. Black also has ideas of ... Rd8  and ... cxd4  at an opportune moment, going for a healthy Grünfeld endgame where White's center can quickly become a liability. }( { A sample continuation is }12.Nf3 Nc6 13.Rc1 cxd4 14.cxd4 Rac8 { Black was very comfortable in ½-½ (41) Morovic Fernandez,I (2575)-De la Villa Garcia,J  (2490) Leon 1995. } )( { In case of }12.Rc1 { , Black should forego the immediate }12...Nc6 { on account of }13.d5 { and instead go for   }12...e6 13.Nf3 { and here }13...Bb5 { getting the light-squared bishops off the board is very interesting. After }14.Bxb5 Qxb5= { White's light-squares are weak and Black has ideas of ... cxd4  followed by ... Rd8  and ... Nc6  to home in on the  d4  pawn. } )
