11. Nd2
11. O-O{ Practice has shown that White doesn't have enough for the pawn. Black scores massively in this position with over a 60% win rate. A typical plan here is ...  Qc7  to prepare the ... e5  break. In some cases, Black can also rapidly mobilize the f-pawn with ... f5 . It's important to note that the  c8  bishop should not come out to  b7 , where it is very passive. It's better placed on  c8  and can come out to  e6 - d5  depending on how White proceeds. }( { A sample continuation is }12.Bf3 Ra7 13.O-O Qc7 14.Bg3 e5 15.Be2 Nd7∓ { White had nothing to show for the pawn. Black went on to win in 0-1 (28) Murdzia,P (2449) -Kasimdzhanov,R (2699) Germany 2013. } )
