5. Qa4+{ Despite being far less popular than 5.  Qb3 , this queen check has been seen in a couple of top level games. White wants to provoke ... Bd7  and only then retreat the queen to  b3 . The first player hopes to prove that the  b7  pawn is unprotected and the bishop is misplaced on  d7 .     I should also point out that the inclusion of  Nf3  such that the  d4  pawn is protected gives this check more bite than the immediate 4.Qa4+  variation. }
5. Bd7
6. Qb3( 6.Qd1 { is obviously harmless. Black can repeat with }6...Bc8 { but we're playing for a win with }6...dxc4 7.e4 c5! 8.d5 O-O { Black is in excellent shape with ... e6  coming next to undermine White's center. } )
6. dxc4
7. Qxb7
