12. Qe4( { The endgame after }12.Qd5 Nb6 13.Qxd8 Rxd8 14.Bf4 Ra7= { is more than fine for Black with strong pressure on the  d4  pawn. } )
12. Nb6{ protects the rook on  h8  while clearing the way for a future ... Bf5 . }
13. Be3
13. b4{ Novel and strong! There's no need to rush with ... Bf5 . Instead, Black first hampers White's development by forcing the  c3  knight back. }( 13...Bf5 14.Qh4 Nc6 15.g4 e5 { was objectively fine for Black in ½-½ (29) Shankland,S (2704) -Vachier Lagrave,M (2761) Berlin 2022, but I see no need to allow any of this. } )
14. Ne2
14. Nd5{ With ideas of ... Bf5  and ... c5 , I already prefer Black's position. White is still several tempi away from getting his king to safety. }
