3. Bg7( 3...b5!? { This Benko like break is also interesting. } )
4. Nc3
4. O-O
5. e4
5. d6{ Black has a turbo-charged version of the King's Indian with White's d-pawn prematurely committed to  d5 . The second player will look to undermine it with either ... e6  and ... c6 . }
6. Bd3
