10. Na5{ The ... e5  break now makes little sense so we're going to instead undermine White's center with ... c6 . }
11. Nd4{ prevents ... c6  but only temporarily. }
11. Bd7{ All of Black's pieces are in the game and ... c6  (or ... c5  now that White's knight is on  d4 ) is coming very soon. }
12. e4
12. c6
13. Re1
13. cxd5
14. exd5
14. Qc8{ preparing ... Bg4  gives Black excellent play. ... Nac4  to pressure White's queenside is also coming. }
