2. Nf3
2. g6
3. e3{ The  Colle  system, also known as the  Colle-Koltanowski  system, is named after the Belgian masters Edgard Colle and George Koltanowski.      Characterized by the moves 2.  Nf3  and 3.  e3 , White usually develops his light-squared bishop to  d3 , the queenside knight to  d2 , and tries to engineer the pawn break  e3 - e4 . White typically reinforces the  d4  pawn with  c2 - c3  in response to ... c5 , setting up a triangle or pyramidal pawn structure with pawns on  f2 ,  e3 ,  d4 ,  c3 , and  b2 .      Nowadays, this variation is considered innocuous as it does  not  put any pressure on the center and restricts White’s dark-squared bishop. It is a popular system at the club level mainly because it can be learned very quickly and is of very low maintenance.     It is particularly ineffective against the fianchetto with 2... g6  as White lacks control over the key  e5  square and the second player can quickly undermine White's center with the ... c5  break. }
3. Bg7
4. Bd3{ has been played 3500+ times OTB. }( 4.b3 { has featured in 600+ OTB games. } )( 4.Be2 { has been played in 2000+ OTB games. } )( 4.c4 { transposes to the 3.Nf3 4.e3  variation. } )
