7. c4{ is the only critical continuation. }( 7.c3 { is obviously harmless. Black can follow suit with }7...c6 8.Nd2 { and then neutralize White's knight on  e5  with }8...Nbd7 9.Ndf3 Nxe5 10.Nxe5 Nd7= { . } )
7. c5{ is rare with only a handful of games in the database but very dynamic. It sets White problem as early as move 7. We will consider three possibilities: 8.  e3 , 8.  dxc5  and 8.  cxd5 , which is already a novelty. }
