11. Nc3
11. dxc4{ This materialistic approach is very strong. Yes, the  c6  pawn is dropping and we opened up White's light-squared bishop. However, once White captures on  c6 , the bishop won't be doing much as there are no longer any targets on the long diagonal.     Ok, what did we achieve with ... dxc4  apart from temporarily winning a pawn? The main point is that the  d4  pawn is now a big target and we're already threatening to win it with ... Bd3  followed by ... Qxd4 . The engines are already giving Black a clear advantage. }
12. Qa4( 12.Bxc6?! { is dubious. After }12...Rb8 13.Re1 e6 { improves over the game 0-1 (29) Brito Garcia,A  (2350)-Hernandez Guerrero,G (2555) Zaragoza 1996. Next up is ... Bd3  when the  d4  pawn will drop. Black already has a decisive advantage. } )
