20. e6{ ... Nd7  is coming next and, if allowed, Black can even take over with ... e5 . I couldn't find a single way for White to ask any questions. }( { In fact, White is advised to simplify with }21.Nxc6 bxc6 22.Qxa6 { and recoup the pawn. Here, }22...Nd7! { is precise. Black not only prepares ... e5 , but threatens ... Nxc5  as the  c3  knight is loose. }23.Ne2 e5= { Black has no problems. } )
