10. axb5
11. hxg4
11. Nxc4
12. Rc1{ Giri uncorked this enterprising move against Nepo back in 2020. He did go on to lose the game, but Black needs to know a thing or two here. }
12. d5{ Black expands in the center and reinforces the  c4  knight. }
13. b3{ We're a pawn up so White can't afford to wait around and allow us to consolidate with ... Bd7 . }
13. Bb4{ A very strong counterblow. Black ignores the threat on the  c4  knight and goes after its counterpart on  c3 . }
14. bxc4
