9. Qh5{ The queen swings to the other side of the board where it still supports the ... d5  break. The one drawback of  Bd2  is that White's queen on  d1  no longer eyes the  d5  square. }
10. Be2
10. d5{ White has no good discoveries with the  f3  knight so Black wastes no time getting in  d5 . }
11. cxd5
11. exd5
12. exd5
12. Nxd5{ White's center has been liquidated and with it any hopes for an advantage. }( {  (a)  }13.Nd4 Qh4 14.Nxc6 bxc6 { White has weakened Black's queenside structure but did give the second player the b-file to play with. The  b2  pawn is particularly vulnerable. }15.O-O Be6 16.Bf3 Rab8= { The  b2  pawn is just as weak as the one on  c6 . Black was fine in ½-½ (45) So,W (2760) -Nepomniachtchi,I (2767) Jerusalem 2019 } )( {  (b)  }13.O-O { is the most natural continuation. }13...Nxc3 14.Bxc3 Qg6= { With ideas of ... Bf6  to neutralize the  c3  bishop and the threat of ... Bh3 , Black had good play in ½-½ (38) Svidler,P (2723) -Nepomniachtchi,I (2784) chess24.com INT 2020. } )
