7. Qxd5{ Black centralizes the queen and is ready to take on  c5 . }
8. Qxd5
8. Nxd5
9. O-O
9. Rd8{ Having defended the  d5  knight, Black is now ready to recoup the c-pawn with ... Na6xc5 . }
10. Rd1{ is the only way to prevent the aforementioned plan. }( 9...Na6 { now fails to }10.e4 { as the  d8  rook lacks protection. } )
10. Nc6{ The c-pawn isn't running away, so Black continues developing normally. The knight comes out to  c6  to protect the  d8  rook, thus neutralizing White's  e4  threat, and ... Bf5  and ... Rc8  are up next. The only way for White to meaningfully disrupt this development plan is to play 11.  e4 . }
11. e4
11. Ndb4
12. Rxd8+
12. Nxd8
13. Nc3
13. Be6{ Black's rook is about to come to  c8  when the c-pawn will drop. Black has no problems whatsoever. }
