{ Should Black go for ... O-O  or first play ... Nc6 ? }7. Nc6{ is the way to go here . A  rule of thumb  in the Grünfeld is that when there's a choice between pressuring the  d4  pawn (with ... Nc6 , ... c5  or ... Bg4 ) and castling, Black should usually go for the former. }( { Concretely, }7...O-O { in this position allows }8.Nc3 Nc6 9.d5 { and after }9...Na5 { White has a pleasant choice between }10.e4 { and }10.Qc2 { . While playable, there's no need to give White the chance to kick our knight to  a5  and expand in the center uncontested. } )
